Created by Zam

This piece is a continuation of my 'Marilyn Morph II' series. This collection usually has its home on Known Origin, here https://knownorigin.io/zam Marilyn (Icecream Sundae) has been created especially to raise funds for Digital Plastic’s ‘Art for Humanity’ charity project facilitated by Simon Beglau (Actual_Simo).

 It will essentially provide 500 packs of Art materials to be distributed to communities in under-resourced countries; and then teach them how to create NFTs of the pieces they then create using the supplies.

ART FOR HUMANITY - STORIES COLLECTION

Mission Statement:


Digital Plastic based in Vancouver, Canada is fund raising with the use of donated NFT art to procure (10) classrooms worth of art supplies (50 individual packages to each class). 

The art supplies consist of 12 tubes of 125ml acrylic paint, 30 page canvas art book, 3 brushes, 1 pencil and 1 eraser.
 

The supplies will delivered to the local under-resourced institutions in the following four (4) locations:


1) Cameroon, Central Africa.

2) Lagos in, Nigeria, Africa.

3) Ayetoro in Nigeria, Africa.

4) Santo Domingo in Dominican Republic.

 
The local correspondents will receive the packages along with (2) educational workshop videos and arrange for a select group of students at the respected institutions to accept and start producing physical art. Once the art is complete the Digital Plastic team will digitize the art and capture each pieces of art stories from the creators. Digital Plastic will mint the newly created 500 pcs collection on the blockchain with a simple smart contract dividing up the proceeds equally between the artist, the institution and a local charity. ​

The goal is to provide an outlet for the artist, school and community to improve the current local situation.

​Each artist will receive a portion of the sale directly either in their local currency or in a cryptocurrency of their choice. This will be decided prior to the minting process specific to each artists direct needs.​

We appreciate everything this NFT space and community has made possible for us all. We want everyone to know this an absolutely amazing opportunity to not only create art, but to save the world as we do it :)

UPDATE:  The art supplies have been manufactured and landed in Vancouver.  We are currently producing our two educational workshop videos and planning for our trip to Cameroon and Nigeria in Africa.  We are planning to arrive with supplies in Q2 of 2022.
